      "writtenOn": "2018-11-16T18:55:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m tempted to just say we don\u0027t care.  I think it\u0027s okay to just say we\u0027re reporting the rate of confirmed flakes as opposed to the actual flakiness rate.  For our purposes I think it\u0027s accurate enough.  For a slightly lower real flake rate of 20%, we\u0027d have something like 25 commits in which the first task failed 5 times and the retry succeeded 4 out of those 5.  So, we have 4 confirmed flakes out of 30 tasks, or 13.3%.  What we really care about is whether or not a given bot is flaky (ie. beyond some base rate of general intermittent infra failures) and when the flakiness rate (for a given bot and/or overall) changes.",
      "parentUuid": "4004fc6a_03f624bd",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 141,
        "startChar": 2,
